==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Trademarked by the {{w|Milton Bradley Company}} in 1956, as an alteration of "Yatzie", derived from {{m|en|yacht}} (see {{w|Yacht (dice game)}}).
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈjɑːtsi/}}
* {{hyph|en|Yaht|zee}}
===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# {{lb|en|dice}} A [[probability]] game where players amass [[score]]s depending on the values of the five [[dice]] they roll.
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# In the game of Yahtzee, a five-of-a-kind, where all dice show the same value, which is the highest-scoring combination.
